{"id": 113980, "acmi_id": "183634", "title": "Mad Max", "title_annotation": "", "slug": "mad-max", "creator_credit": "George Miller", "credit_line": "<p>Courtesy Roadshow Films Pty Ltd</p>", "headline_credit": "Australia, 1979", "thumbnail": {"image_url": "https://acmi-public-api.s3.amazonaws.com/image/183634_MadMaxPoster_TMDB.jpg.1200x1200_q85.jpg", "has_video": false}, "record_type": "work", "type": "Film", "is_on_display": true, "last_on_display_place": "ACMI: Gallery 1", "last_on_display_date": "2031-02-16", "is_context_indigenous": false, "material_description": "", "unpublished": false, "first_production_date": "1979-01-01T11:00:00+11:00", "brief_description": "<p>George Miller&#8217;s Mad Max revolutionised movies when it tore through cinemas in 1979. Bursting with stunning practical effects, explosive set pieces and iconic costumes, the original Mad Max trilogy (1979-85) cemented its place in pop culture before roaring back to life 30 years later.</p>", "constellations_primary": [], "constellations_other": [{"id": 83, "name": "Evil AI, dystopias and production design", "description": "In No Code’s sci-fi thriller players take command of a multi-national space station’s artificial intelligence system to help the sole survivor solve the mystery of a missing crew and why the station is wildly off course."}], "recommendations": [], "title_for_label": "<p>Mad Max</p>", "creator_credit_for_label": "<p>George Miller</p>", "headline_credit_for_label": "<p>Australia, 1979</p>", "description": "<p>Starring the then little known Mel Gibson, this low-budget box-office smash also launched the career of director George Miller and would be followed up by three more sequels. Set in a post-apocalyptic lawless world, <i>Mad Max</i> can be credited for inventing a genre and opening up the global market for Australian films.</p>\n<p>The seeds were planted for Miller&#8217;s thrilling post-apocalyptic Oscar winning opus, <i>Mad Max Fury Road</i> with his debut film which set the bar for breathtaking car stunts and brutal violence. Using to great effect iconic Melbourne locations such as the Melbourne University car park and Victoria’s expansive country roads, it’s a wonder that this now classic and highly influential film didn’t spearhead an Australian film industry made up of post-apocalyptic road movies.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Stunts themselves would be nothing without a filmmaker behind the camera and George Miller, a doctor and film buff making his first feature, shows he knows what cinema is all about&#8221; - <i>Variety</i></p>", "description_for_label": ["<p>Starring the then little known Mel Gibson, this low-budget box-office smash also launched the career of director George Miller and would be followed up by three more sequels. Set in a post-apocalyptic lawless world, <i>Mad Max</i> can be credited for inventing a genre and opening up the global market for Australian films.</p>\n<p>The seeds were planted for Miller&#8217;s thrilling post-apocalyptic Oscar winning opus, <i>Mad Max Fury Road</i> with his debut film which set the bar for breathtaking car stunts and brutal violence. Using to great effect iconic Melbourne locations such as the Melbourne University car park and Victoria’s expansive country roads, it’s a wonder that this now classic and highly influential film didn’t spearhead an Australian film industry made up of post-apocalyptic road movies.</p>\n<p>&#8220;Stunts themselves would be nothing without a filmmaker behind the camera and George Miller, a doctor and film buff making his first feature, shows he knows what cinema is all about&#8221; - <i>Variety</i></p>"], "credit_line_for_label": "<p>Courtesy Roadshow Films Pty Ltd</p>", "details": [{"label": "Curatorial section", "display_values": ["The Story of the Moving Image&nbsp;→ Moving Australia&nbsp;→ 03. Car Culture&nbsp;→ MA-03-C01"]}], "stats": {"tap_count": 0}, "links": [{"url": "https://www.justwatch.com/au/movie/mad-max", "title": "Stream, rent or buy at <span>JustWatc